reviewText: I was attracted to the great collection of comics all on one DVD. I have not finished viewing it yet. I will say, these comics do not get to be themselves though. Their acts seem very to be tuned down being Montreal appears to be very conservative compared to us here in the U.S.A.
Very funny collection of standup acts
Funny as hell. About 10 min. each, so, if they suck, there's another one coming along. I liked them all.

I got this dvd because it has Mitch Hedberg.  Of course Lewis Black is always funny, and it's interesting to see a younger Jim Gaffigan (with glasses and slimmer).  It made my boyfriend and I both laugh.

A classic performance by Mitch Hedberg is the main reason for purchasing this DVD, but the other performers are fun to watch also.  I just wish there was more material on this wonderful comedian who left us all too soon.
